Description: Corroded copper alloy stud with a round head of parabolic profile. In the middle of the hollow underside remains part of a narrow shank, of rectangular cross-section, broken at the end.
Curator's comments: One of the "nail-heads" of "parabolic" form, mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 80 § 80.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 80 § 80)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.80, p.186, pl.28)
Condition: fair, incomplete (part of the shank broken and missing)
